{"key":"post-11105416","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>11105416</id>\n<content>Bad idea.&amp;nbsp; Plants can tolerate a steady moisture content.&amp;nbsp; When you allow a mushroom substrate to begin drying out, it's a major pinning trigger.&amp;nbsp; If you wicked moisture into it, performance would be poor.&amp;nbsp; We let our substrates begin to dry out, and then mist to replenish the moisture.&amp;nbsp; The changing moisture state is a signal for fruit formation.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>11105471</next>\n<prev>11105403</prev>\n<first>11105380</first>\n<last>11105717</last>\n<when>1253630787</when>\n<utime>09/22/09 05:46 PM</utime>\n</post>"}